	<TD WIDTH=20%><B>Author</B></TD>
	<TD><B>My answer to healer aggro for the station newbies</B></TD>
</TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#efefef" ALIGN="LEFT">
<TD width=18% valign=top><b>Strikan</b><br>
<font size=1>Newbie Poster</font><BR><font size=1>Joined: Nov 10, 2000</font>
<br><font size=1>Posts: 23<br>
From: <br></FONT>
<img src="images/forum/avatar/003.gif"></td><td><img src="images/forum/icons/posticon.gif"><font size=1>&nbsp;&nbsp;Posted: 2001-02-23 16:34</font><br><br>
Copied from my post from verant's message board in response to a bunch of newbies claiming there was no change to healing, or that it was "good"<BR><BR>Strikan<BR><BR>---------------------------------------------<BR>-----------------------------------<BR>First to reply to all the newbies posting about how there is no problem healing my answer is the following:<BR>1. If your not fighting level 51+ mobs then you are not seeing the full effect of this patch. Because the aggro CAP per heal is MUCH lower for mobs under 51 than it is for level 51+.<BR><BR>Second this is NOT just Complete heal, nor is it limited to clerics. ALL healers are dying, druids, shamans, and clerics.<BR><BR>Second. When you are fighting uber mobs who do upwards of 600+ pts of damage PER combat round that means in order to keep people alive who are taking hits you have to HEAL 600pts per combat round. <BR><BR>Basically what this means is some HEALER is gaining 600+ pts of aggro PER combat round. NO tank, no matter how they are equipped is building up aggro that fast.<BR><BR>Basically what this means is NO matter how you play, no matter what heal you cast, no matter what, if you are fighting mobs that output massive amounts of damage OVER and beyond the amount of aggro a melee can generate the HEALER (cleric,shaman or druid) will be summoned and KILLED if not healed. If you heal the HEALER then you are just aggroing ANOTHER cleric and it gets WORSE from that point on.<BR><BR>What this means is when you are fighting mobs that output significantly more damage than a tank can generate an equivalent amount of hate for you will end up pingponging that mob between your HEALERS.<BR><BR>I've fought in MANY places since the patch, for LONG periods of time.<BR><BR>This patch does NOT effect, or very little effect, when you are fighting mobs < level 51. However when you hit that magic level 51 number things get worse and worse as the mob level goes up, the cap for aggro per heal goes WAY up, and the healing requirements go up.<BR><BR>When mobs hit around level 57-60 (especially 60+ which is what ToV is ALL 60+) the mobs do so much damage it is impossible to not have them chase the cleric after the FIRST heal is cast.<BR><BR>Basically the higher the level the encounter the worse it is.<BR><BR>So please stop saying this patch did nothing, when you don't have the in game experience of fighting level 51-60+ mobs to know how it effects the high level game.<BR><BR>In big encounters clerics are LIMITED to 2 heals max per fight. Because it turns into the following step:<BR>Cleric casts heal.<BR>Cleric casts divine aura<BR>Cleric casts heal<BR>Cleric case Divine barrier.<BR><BR>Cleric can then not heal for another 15 minutes or risk death due to aggro.<BR><BR>Druids just plain die after the first heal. Shamans just straight up die also.<BR><BR>Another point of interest you might want to consider.<BR><BR>Donals BP was changed to be only useable very 7.5 minutes per target.<BR><BR>Clerics have 2 divine aura type spells. Each with a 15 minute recast time. Due to high level aggro in the game you cast 1 divine aura after EACH heal to stay alive. <BR><BR>So in effect what this means is a cleric can use BP every 7.5 minutes. He can also only use CASTABLE heal spells every 7.5 minutes if he doesn't want to risk death IE:<BR><BR>Cast heal.<BR>Divine aura.<BR>Wait 7.5 minutes.<BR>Cast heal<BR>Divine barrier<BR>Wait 7.5 minutes<BR>Now first divine aura is cycled so rinse repeat.<BR><BR>Coincidence on the timing of the BP and this situation? I seriously seriously doubt it. Considering it is acurate down to the second and is not a even number.<BR><BR><BR><HR noshade size=1>
